&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Software Development Engineer in Test (SDET)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Remote&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tuesday Health is a value-based palliative care provider group dedicated to transforming serious illness and end-of-life care. We deliver goal-centered care focused on alleviating physical symptoms and emotional stress for individuals and their caregivers. Our interdisciplinary care teams reduce avoidable hospitalizations and improve quality of life wherever individuals call home. Through our leading-edge care model, Tuesday Health is shaping the future of community-based palliative care nationwide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;The Role:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re hiring our first dedicated SDET to own test automation across our product suite. You&#39;ll design, build, and maintain automated test suites that act as a continuous QA layer for our web, API, and mobile applications. This is a high-ownership role on a small, senior onshore team — your work directly determines how confidently we ship.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A defining feature of this role: we are an AI-forward engineering organization. We use Claude Enterprise heavily across our SDLC, and you&#39;ll leverage it daily to author, update, and maintain test scripts at a pace a traditional QA process can&#39;t match. We&#39;re looking for someone who is energized by that way of working, not resistant to it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key responsibilities of this role may include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own end-to-end test automation &lt;/strong&gt;for our Blazor WebAssembly front end, including UI and functional test suites (e.g., Playwright).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build and maintain API test coverage &lt;/strong&gt;for our .NET Core back-end APIs, Azure Function apps, and dedicated authentication service — integration, contract, and regression testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Establish mobile test automation &lt;/strong&gt;for our .NET MAUI mobile application across iOS and Android.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leverage Claude Enterprise &lt;/strong&gt;to generate, refactor, and maintain test scripts efficiently, and help define best practices for AI-assisted testing on the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Integrate testing into CI/CD &lt;/strong&gt;so automated suites run on every build and release, with clear pass/fail signals and actionable failure reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Track and report quality metrics &lt;/strong&gt;— escaped defects, coverage, flaky test rates — and use them to drive improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner with developers &lt;/strong&gt;to make testability a first-class concern in design and code review, and to reproduce, isolate, and verify bug fixes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perform targeted exploratory testing &lt;/strong&gt;where automation isn&#39;t the right tool, especially for new features and edge cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
